Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.03,0:40:58.95,English,,0,0,0,,so the sacred band of Thebes was forever destroyed.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.45,0:41:03.15,English,,0,0,0,,And the irony of course is, it's the sacred band of Thebes\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.15,0:41:06.07,English,,0,0,0,,that taught Philip how to build a great army.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.09,0:41:09.61,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And in his last act,\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.75,0:41:12.77,English,,0,0,0,,he destroyed the sacred band of Thebes.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.77,0:41:14.81,English,,0,0,0,,And now he united all of Greece.\N{\rChinese}现在他统一了整个希腊。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.25,0:41:16.61,English,,0,0,0,,Now that he united all of Greece,\N{\rChinese}现在他统一了整个希腊，他的大意是把他的军队带到前方去征服…
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.89,0:41:21.53,English,,0,0,0,,his ambition now is to take his army and conquer Persia.\N{\rChinese}现在他统一了整个希腊，把他的军队去往前方…
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.21,0:41:23.91,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So what he did was,\N{\rChinese}好的？他所做的就是，他把大将军Parmenion 送到希尔…
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.03,0:41:29.99,English,,0,0,0,,he sent his great general Parmenion into Persia.\N{\rChinese}好的，...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.09,0:41:33.41,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Remember in Anatolia at this time, which is today Turkey,\N{\rChinese}好的？记得在那时的安纳托利亚，也就是今天的土耳。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.71,0:41:36.53,English,,0,0,0,,there are lots of Greek colonies that are under Persian rule.\N{\rChinese}好的，...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.75,0:41:40.31,English,,0,0,0,,And for the longest time, they wanted to be free of Persian rule.\N{\rChinese}在此期间，...…
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.41,0:41:43.85,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So Parmenion went over with a vanguard,\N{\rChinese}?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.97,0:41:46.85,English,,0,0,0,,about 10,000 men, to begin the invasion.\N{\rChinese}约一万名士兵，开始入侵。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.83,0:41:50.85,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And\N{\rChinese}Okay? And
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.85,0:41:53.63,English,,0,0,0,,Philip was about to go over\N{\rChinese}菲利普正准备出发
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.63,0:41:56.87,English,,0,0,0,,and lead the invasion, but\N{\rChinese}???
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.87,0:41:59.27,English,,0,0,0,,his daughter was about to get married.\N{\rChinese}他的女儿即将成婚。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.39,0:42:02.79,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So he had to attend the wedding. At the wedding,\N{\rChinese}好的？于是他得去参加婚礼。婚礼上，
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.89,0:42:08.19,English,,0,0,0,,he had one bodyguard.\N{\rChinese}他只配备一名随从。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.27,0:42:12.45,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Because at the wedding,\N{\rChinese}好的？因为婚礼上，
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.47,0:42:14.09,English,,0,0,0,,there'll be lots of Greek diplomats, right?\N{\rChinese}有很多希腊外交官员在场上，
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.23,0:42:15.47,English,,0,0,0,,So he wanted to appear approachable.\N{\rChinese}他想要出面相接待。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.61,0:42:17.29,English,,0,0,0,,So he didn't have his entire bodyguard in place.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.47,0:42:18.73,English,,0,0,0,,He had one bodyguard. Okay?\N{\rChinese}他只配备一名随从。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.89,0:42:21.43,English,,0,0,0,,His bodyguard took his sword and\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.43,0:42:23.77,English,,0,0,0,,stabbed him in the rib, killing him.\N{\rChinese}在他肋骨处刺中，击中他。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.39,0:42:27.27,English,,0,0,0,,And then his bodyguard was killed by the other bodyguards.\N{\rChinese}随后其随从被其他随从击中。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.73,0:42:32.99,English,,0,0,0,,So Philip was assassinated before he could launch his invasion of Persia.\N{\rChinese}译文1
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.09,0:42:36.73,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And when he died,\N{\rChinese}译语句
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.93,0:42:38.93,English,,0,0,0,,it was like 337.\N{\rChinese}它大约是337。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.93,0:42:42.09,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Okay?\N{\rChinese}好的？好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.17,0:42:45.15,English,,0,0,0,,So Philip was really in the prime of his life.\N{\rChinese}所以菲利普真的处于人生巅峰。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.05,0:42:48.79,English,,0,0,0,,He had like 30, 40 years of military conquest to go.\N{\rChinese}他有大约30-40年军旅征服之旅程。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.75,0:42:52.19,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? He died very young.\N{\rChinese}好的？他很年轻就去世了。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.21,0:42:57.83,English,,0,0,0,,And his son, Alexander, who was like 18, 19 at this time, he now became king.\N{\rChinese}好的，算起这时，算起这时，算起这个…
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.15,0:43:03.25,English,,0,0,0,,It was Alexander who would lead his army into Persia\N{\rChinese}它是亚历山大去领军去…
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.25,0:43:06.17,English,,0,0,0,,and conquer all Persia and move all the way to India.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.67,0:43:09.41,English,,0,0,0,,Or like the... Or Pakistan, really.\N{\rChinese}或像…或巴基斯坦真的…
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.13,0:43:13.67,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So for the longest time,\N{\rChinese}好的，算起…
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.73,0:43:15.13,English,,0,0,0,,historians do not know what happened.\N{\rChinese}历史上…
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.21,0:43:18.07,English,,0,0,0,,How is it possible for this great man,\N{\rChinese}这位伟人菲利普二世在巅峰时被暗杀，究竟如何？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.17,0:43:20.57,English,,0,0,0,,Philip II, to be assassinated in the prime of his life?\N{\rChinese}菲利普二世在巅峰时被暗杀，究竟是怎样的事？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.97,0:43:22.57,English,,0,0,0,,All right? Now, there are three explanations.\N{\rChinese}菲利普二世在巅峰时被暗士…
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.61,0:43:24.85,English,,0,0,0,,There are three major explanations.\N{\rChinese}有三种主要解释。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.29,0:43:28.37,English,,0,0,0,,The first explanation is it was Persia.\N{\rChinese}第一种解释是波斯人。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.27,0:43:35.99,English,,0,0,0,,Persia knew that Philip was about to invade, and so they hired the bodyguard to kill him.\N{\rChinese}波斯人知道菲利普即将入侵，遂雇佣护卫去杀他。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.07,0:43:37.59,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? That's the first explanation.\N{\rChinese}好的？那是第一个解释。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.95,0:43:40.75,English,,0,0,0,,Second explanation is it was personal.\N{\rChinese}第二个解释是…
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.95,0:43:45.29,English,,0,0,0,,So the story is very complicated, but\N{\rChinese}好的，故事…
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.29,0:43:48.19,English,,0,0,0,,apparently the bodyguard and Philip were lovers.\N{\rChinese}看起来护卫与菲利普是恋人。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.37,0:43:50.79,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? They were homosexual lovers. And then\N{\rChinese}好？他们是同性爱人。然后…
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.79,0:43:54.01,English,,0,0,0,,Philip found someone else, and the bodyguard became very jealous.\N{\rChinese}菲利普又找了别人，护卫很嫉妒。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.67,0:43:56.11,English,,0,0,0,,So it's a very complicated story.\N{\rChinese}译文1
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.21,0:43:59.03,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? It was personal. And then there's one more explanation.\N{\rChinese}译文2
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.33,0:44:04.63,English,,0,0,0,,The other explanation was it was the mother of Alexander,\N{\rChinese}译文3
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.89,0:44:07.35,English,,0,0,0,,Olympias. And Alexander.\N{\rChinese}奥利米亚斯。还有亚历山大。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.67,0:44:10.41,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Right?\N{\rChinese}好？对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.41,0:44:13.11,English,,0,0,0,,So these are the three explanations.\N{\rChinese}于是这三种解释。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.93,0:44:19.65,English,,0,0,0,,So if you want to, and like, honestly, we'll never ever know what happened.\N{\rChinese}So if you want to, and like, honestly, we'll never ever know what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.73,0:44:24.21,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? But if you want to evaluate a murder, you always look at two things.\N{\rChinese}好的？但如果你想评估一次谋杀，你总是先看两件事。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.67,0:44:28.79,English,,0,0,0,,Look at opportunity. Who\N{\rChinese}看着机会。谁
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.79,0:44:30.23,English,,0,0,0,,has the chance to kill him?\N{\rChinese}有机会杀他吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.33,0:44:32.51,English,,0,0,0,,You look at motive. Okay?\N{\rChinese}你看着点子
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.71,0:44:35.47,English,,0,0,0,,You understand? So if you look at these two things, you look at opportunity.\N{\rChinese}\}]
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.23,0:44:38.05,English,,0,0,0,,Let's evaluate all three possibilities.\N{\rChinese}?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.05,0:44:43.17,English,,0,0,0,,Persia. Okay. It had the motive, but it didn't have the opportunity.\N{\rChinese}波斯。好的。它有动机，但也没能得时机。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.77,0:44:48.25,English,,0,0,0,,You understand? How could it access Philip's inner court?\N{\rChinese}你们好？…
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.43,0:44:50.03,English,,0,0,0,,Right? And Philip's not a dumb guy.\N{\rChinese}对吧？菲利普也不是个傻瓜。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.23,0:44:51.97,English,,0,0,0,,He would know exactly who to trust and who not to trust.\N{\rChinese}他会知道谁能接着谁不接着。”
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.65,0:44:56.49,English,,0,0,0,,And usually, if Persia was afraid of Philip,\N{\rChinese}And usually, if Persiawas afraid of Philip,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.59,0:45:00.47,English,,0,0,0,,what they could do was basically give Sparta\N{\rChinese}...
